==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tudor
<hw>Tu"dor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to a
royal line of England, descended from Owen <ets>Tudor</ets> of Wales,
who married the widowed queen of Henry V. The first reigning Tudor was
Henry VII.; the last, Elizabeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tudor style</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>the latest
development of Gothic architecture in England, under the Tudors,
characterized by flat four-centered arches, shallow moldings, and a
profusion of paneling on the walls.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tue</ent>⟦br⟧
